benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/catalog - Delete all versions for a per tenant catalog

covered: Valid deletion scenarios (TC01, TC02, TC15) delete all catalog versions and return 204
Tenant with no catalog versions (TC05) results in 204 and no changes
Concurrency handling (TC13) ensures system remains consistent
Authorization/header validation (TC03, TC04, TC07, TC14) ensures proper error handling for missing/invalid headers
Error handling (TC09) returns 500 on system failure
Security edge cases (TC11) for malicious header payload
Data integrity check (TC12) ensures no orphaned references
Extra headers (TC08) are ignored and deletion proceeds
Performance/large dataset (TC10) verifies deletion completes within time
Post-delete verification (GET after deletion) confirms empty/404
gaps: Soft delete semantics not explicitly tested (hard vs soft delete behavior)
Rate limiting tests for bursts of DELETE requests
Caching behavior: testing for caching headers on DELETE responses or confirming they are not cached
403 Forbidden scenario: authenticated user lacks necessary permissions
Cross-tenant isolation test to ensure other tenants are unaffected by deletion
Explicit idempotency testing for repeated deletes beyond concurrent scenario
recommendations: Add a test to validate soft-delete semantics and whether data is permanently removed or marked deleted
Add rate-limiting/throttling tests for DELETE endpoint
Add caching headers validation for DELETE responses if applicable, or confirm they are not cached
Add a 403 Forbidden scenario for authorized user without proper permissions
Clarify and expand TC13 to cover explicit idempotency behavior for repeated deletes
